## 3) API Client Extensions

### 3.1 Types
- Add:
  - `src/types/profile.ts`
  - `src/types/settings.ts`

#### `src/types/profile.ts` (proposed shapes)
- `Profile` (self or public, frontend view model):
  - `id: string`
  - `displayName: string`
  - `username: string`
  - `bio: string | null`
  - `location: string | null`
  - `avatarUrl: string | null`
  - `joinDate: string` (ISO string; formatted as "Joined Month Year" in UI)
  - `followersCount: number`
  - `followingCount: number`
  - `isDiscoverable: boolean`
  - `showLocation: boolean`
- Responses:
  - `GetMyProfileResponse: Profile`
  - `GetPublicProfileResponse: Profile` (backend will omit private/account-only fields as needed).
- Mutations:
  - `UpdateProfilePayload` (all optional fields):
    - `displayName?: string`
    - `bio?: string | null`
    - `location?: string | null`
    - `isDiscoverable?: boolean`
    - `showLocation?: boolean`
- Avatar:
  - `AvatarUploadUrlPayload`:
    - `filename: string`
    - `contentType: string`
    - `fileSize: number`
  - `AvatarUploadUrlResponse`:
    - `uploadUrl: string`
    - `avatarKey: string` (or similar storage key ÔÇô aligns with backend)
  - `ConfirmAvatarPayload`:
    - `avatarKey: string`

#### `src/types/settings.ts`
- `SettingsResponse`:
  - `email: string`
  - `legalName?: string | null`
  - `emailNotificationsEnabled: boolean`
  - `marketingEmailsEnabled: boolean`
  - `platformUpdatesEnabled: boolean`
  - `isDiscoverable: boolean`
  - `showLocation: boolean`
- `UpdateSettingsPayload`:
  - Partial of the toggles above (all optional; email/legalName excluded).

### 3.2 `src/services/apiClient.ts` Additions
- `profile` namespace:
  - `profile.me(): Promise<GetMyProfileResponse>` Ôćĺ `GET /profile/me`
  - `profile.byHandle(handle: string): Promise<GetPublicProfileResponse>` Ôćĺ `GET /profile/${handle}` (or `/profile/[handle]`; actual path matches backend).
  - `profile.update(payload: UpdateProfilePayload): Promise<GetMyProfileResponse>` Ôćĺ `PATCH /profile`
  - `profile.requestAvatarUpload(payload: AvatarUploadUrlPayload): Promise<AvatarUploadUrlResponse>` Ôćĺ `POST /profile/avatar/upload-url`
  - `profile.confirmAvatar(payload: ConfirmAvatarPayload): Promise<{ avatarUrl: string }>` Ôćĺ `POST /profile/avatar/confirm`
  - `profile.removeAvatar(): Promise<void>` Ôćĺ `DELETE /profile/avatar`
- `settings` namespace:
  - `settings.get(): Promise<SettingsResponse>` Ôćĺ `GET /settings`
  - `settings.update(payload: UpdateSettingsPayload): Promise<SettingsResponse>` Ôćĺ `PATCH /settings`

> All API methods will use the existing `request<T>()` helper and `ApiError` for consistent error handling.

## 4) Containers (Smart Components)

> All containers live under `src/components/containers`, call `apiClient` (no inline `fetch`), manage loading/error/empty, and pass plain props to dumb UI components.

### 4.1 Layout
- `src/components/containers/layout/AppShellContainer.tsx` (client):
  - Uses `usePathname()` (from `next/navigation`) to determine active nav item.
  - Optionally calls `apiClient.user.me()` to get a lightweight user summary (id, email, displayName, username, avatarUrl from profile if available later).
  - Renders `AppShell` UI component with:
    - `activeRoute`, `userSummary`, `children`.

### 4.2 Profile
- `src/components/containers/profile/MyProfilePageContainer.tsx`:
  - Fetches self profile via `apiClient.profile.me()`.
  - States:
    - Loading Ôćĺ skeletons.
    - Error (401) Ôćĺ prompt to log in.
    - Error (other) Ôćĺ generic error banner.
    - Success Ôćĺ render `ProfilePage` UI with normalized `Profile` prop and self-view flag.
- `src/components/containers/profile/UserProfilePageContainer.tsx`:
  - Takes `handle` from route params.
  - Calls `apiClient.profile.byHandle(handle)`.
  - States:
    - Loading Ôćĺ skeleton.
    - 404 Ôćĺ ÔÇťUser not foundÔÇŁ empty state.
    - Error Ôćĺ generic error.
    - Success Ôćĺ `ProfilePage` UI with public view flag (no edit, no private fields).
- `src/components/containers/profile/EditProfileContainer.tsx`:
  - Loads `profile.me()` and populates form state.
  - Submits `profile.update()` on Save.
  - Manages:
    - Dirty vs clean state (Save disabled when nothing changed).
    - Inline validation:
      - Display name required, max 50 chars.
      - Bio max 160 chars.
      - Location max 100 chars.
    - Success Ôćĺ shows toast ÔÇťProfile updatedÔÇŁ, optionally notifies a shared profile cache (future).
    - Error Ôćĺ inline field errors if backend returns validation details; fallback to generic toast.
  - Integrates `AvatarUploader` component and avatar API methods for upload/replace/remove.

### 4.3 Settings
- `src/components/containers/settings/SettingsPageContainer.tsx`:
  - Fetches `settings.get()`.
  - Renders sections:
    - Account (email, legalName ÔÇô read-only).
